Then, the Blessed One addressed those monks: “Monks, all conditioned states are impermanent, uncertain, unreliable, subject to change. This being the case, monks, one should become disgusted with,
            indifferent to, not fixated upon, Sanskrit omits. and liberated from all conditioned states. Cf. MPS 48.14;
              NidSa 7.3,4; DN II 198.18–23; SN II 178; and SN III 147.
